cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on the recognition of handwritten Arabic digits using deep learning techniques, specifically stacked autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these fields are closely related to the use of deep learning techniques for image recognition and classification tasks.
